FBIS3-33437 "drlat037_o_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-037 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Feb 1994 Colombia Ministry Requests Information PA2402020794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 24 Feb 94 PA2402020794 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] The Colombian Foreign Ministry issued a communique tonight requesting official information from the United States on the services provided by Maria del Rosario Casas to the CIA in Mexico. The ministry is also requesting information on why Aldrich Ames, her husband, went to Colombia. In addition, the Foreign Ministry asked the prosecutor general and the attorney general to investigate Maria del Rosario Casas' conduct. On this same issue, Noemi Sanin, Colombian foreign minister, has already offered the U.S. Government her full cooperation with the investigation into Maria del Rosario Casas' involvement in the case, the most talked-about spy case in recent times. Meanwhile, the Registrar's Office has disclosed the identification card of the accused. The Foreign Ministry received orders today to maintain under strict reserve the curriculum vitae of Maria del Rosario Casas du Puy, Colombian Mata Hari captured by the FBI in the United States. She is accused of spying for Russia. This is Casas du Puy's photograph when she applied for a diplomatic post in Mexico. [video shows photograph of Maria del Rosario Casas] Here is what Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin has said: [Begin Sanin recording] She is a well-known person from an established family. We hope, due to her background, she will be found innocent of the charges; if not, she must surrender to justice, because the accusations of the crime she has allegedly committed are very serious. [end recording]
